                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A silt frog can eat spells and magical effects, removing them from a creature. The silt frog makes a jaws Strike. If the Strike hits and deals damage, the frog attempts to ingest the highest spell or magical effect currently affecting the target, using the result of its Strike as a counteract check. If the silt frog successfully counteracts the effect, it ingests the magic, regaining @Damage[10[healing]] Hit Points. Regardless of the result, the silt frog can't use Ingest Magic again for [[/gmr 1d4 #Recharge Ingest Magic]]{1d4 rounds}.</p>"
                },
